HEADWORD: Sleazy
<hw>Slea"zy</hw> <pr>(sl⟦emac⟧"z⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. G.
<ets>schleissig</ets> worn out, threadbare, from <ets>schleissen</ets>
to slit, split, decay, or E. <ets>leasy</ets>.]</ety> <def>Lacking
firmness of texture or substance; thin; flimsy; <as>as, <ex>sleazy</ex>
silk or muslin</as>.</def> <altsp>[Spelt also
<asp>slazy</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

